RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELTA DOWNS RACE 1 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 78. Claiming Purse 13000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BELLA'S GATSBY was unruly in the gates, broke out, pressed the pace, moved up around the final turn, drove clear down the lane and won under steady urging. LOST GOLD lacked early speed, racing on the rail down the backside, moved up around the final turn, angled out, split rivals, proved no match for the winner, but got up for second. QUIET AS MIDNIGHT was fractious in the gates before the start, raced near the back, came around the final turn four wide, rallied and was outfinished for second. GHOST COWBOY raced in the back of the pack in the beginning, made a late gain and missed the show position. WINGS OF GOLD vied for the early lead and weakened late. PRESUMPTIVE CLOSER went to the front, drove clear, saved ground and faded. WILDCARD GOLD was fractious in the gates, raced in the middle of the field, dropped back and was no threat late. PRINCE SIMBA raced within contention in the beginning, came around the first turn four wide, retreated and was outrun.
